verflow.com/questions/tagged/couchdb\">Stack Overflow</a>-like interface.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"http://people.apache.org/committers-by-project.html#couchdb\"><img class=\"emoji-icon\" alt=\"emoji-star2\" data-icon=\"emoji-star2\" style=\"display: inline; margin: 0; margin-top: 1px; position: relative; top: 5px; width: 25px\" src=\"data:image/png;base64, \" title=\"emoji-star2\" /><strong>The</strong> <em><strong>Amazing</strong></em> <strong>CouchDB Committers</strong> <em>and</em> <strong>Project Managers</strong> <img class=\"emoji-icon\" alt=\"emoji-heart_eyes_cat\" data-icon=\"emoji-heart_eyes_cat\" style=\"display: inline; margin: 0; margin-top: 1px; position: relative; top: 5px; width: 25px\" src=\"data:image/png;base64, \" title=\"emoji-heart_eyes_cat\" /></a></p>\n<h3 id=\"companies\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#companies\" aria-label=\"companies permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Companies</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/eHealthAfrica\">eHealth Africa</a> - Big user of CouchDB, check out their <a href=\"https://github.com/eHealthAfrica/couchdb-best-practices\">best practices</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/eHealthAfrica/couchdb-best-practices\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">277</span></span></a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"hosting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hosting\" aria-label=\"hosting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hosting</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cloudant.com/\">Cloudant</a> - Distributed database as a service (DBaaS).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.smileupps.com/\">Smileupps</a> - CouchDB hosting.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://bitnami.com/stack/couchdb/cloud/google\">Bitnami Launchpad for Google Cloud Platform</a> - Host CouchDB on Google Cloud Platform.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"related-projects\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#related-projects\" aria-label=\"related projects permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Related Projects</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://pouchdb.com/\">PouchDB</a> - A pocket-sized database.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.foundationdb.org/\">FoundationDB</a> - CouchDB 4.0 will utilize FoundationDB.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://hood.ie/\">Hoodie</a> - A backend for Offline First applications.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.couchbase.com/\">Couchbase</a> - NoSQL database.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.couchbase.com/server/current/install/migrate-couchdb.html\">Migrating from Apache CouchDB</a> - Comparison of CouchDB and CouchBase</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"misctechnical\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#misctechnical\" aria-label=\"misctechnical permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Misc/Technical</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20160311144130/https://cloudant.com/blog/dynamo-and-couchdb-clusters/#.WIEp4xsrKUk\">Dynamo and CouchDB Clusters</a> - Article about scaling CouchDB, using clusters.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://research.google.com/archive/sawzall.html\">Google’s paper on Sawzall</a> - Exotic Reductions Examples.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.dimagi.com/blog/what-every-developer-should-know-about-couchdb/\">What Every Developer Should Know About CouchDB</a> - Article about lessons learned.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.nosql.se/2011/09/couchdb-maximum-database-size/\">CouchDB Maximum Database Size</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://horicky.blogspot.com/2009/11/nosql-patterns.html\">NOSQL Patterns</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://eclipsesource.com/blogs/2009/12/13/persistent-trees-in-git-clojure-and-couchdb-data-structure-convergence/\">Persistent Trees in git, Clojure and CouchDB</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://pozorvlak.livejournal.com/176385.html\">CouchDB - JSON and B-trees and REST, oh my!</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"attachments\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#attachments\" aria-label=\"attachments permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Attachments</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://pouchdb.com/2014/06/17/12-pro-tips-for-better-code-with-pouchdb.html\">PouchDB - Attachments are overrated</a> - <em>\"Update: since this post was written, the stability and performance of attachments in PouchDB has greatly improved. ...\"</em></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.cloudant.com/attachments.html#performance-considerations\">Cloudant - Attachments Performance Considerations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://grokbase.com/t/couchdb/user/14a1phbzrb/are-attachments-duplicated-for-each-revision-as-well\">Are attachments duplicated for each revision?</a> - Mailing list discussion about attachments across revisions.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"backups\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#backups\" aria-label=\"backups permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.0